Fidel Castro In 2006 he transferred his responsibilities to Vice-President Castro , who was elected to the presidency by the National Assembly in 2008 . Fidel Castro Abroad , Castro supported anti-imperialist revolutionary groups , backing the establishment of Marxist governments in Chile , Nicaragua , and Grenada , and sending troops to aid allies in the Yom Kippur War , Ogaden War , and Angolan Civil War . Fidel Castro Policies introducing central economic planning and expanding healthcare and education were accompanied by state control of the press and the suppression of internal dissent . claim: James VI and I was a leader.
evidence: James VI and I Since the latter half of the 20th century , historians have tended to revise James 's reputation and treat him as a serious and thoughtful monarch . James VI and I The kingdoms of Scotland and England were individual sovereign states , with their own parliaments , judiciary , and laws , though both were ruled by James in personal union . James VI and I In his reign , the Plantation of Ulster and British colonization of the Americas began . James VI and I James VI and I 19 June 1566 -- 27 March 1625 was King of Scotland as James VI from 24 July 1567 and King of England and Ireland as James I from the union of the Scottish and English crowns on 24 March 1603 until his death . James VI and I In 1603 , he succeeded the last Tudor monarch of England and Ireland , Elizabeth I , who died without issue . James VI and I After the Union of the Crowns , he based himself in England the largest of the three realms from 1603 , only returning to Scotland once in 1617 , and styled himself `` King of Great Britain and Ireland '' . James VI and I Four different regents governed during his minority , which ended officially in 1578 , though he did not gain full control of his government until 1583 . James VI and I He continued to reign in all three kingdoms for 22 years , a period known after him as the Jacobean era , until his death in 1625 at the age of 58 . James VI and I James succeeded to the Scottish throne at the age of thirteen months , after his mother Mary was compelled to abdicate in his favour . James VI and I James was the son of Mary , Queen of Scots , and a great-great-grandson of Henry VII , King of England and Lord of Ireland , positioning him to eventually accede to all three thrones . James VI and I At 57 years and 246 days , James 's reign in Scotland was longer than those of any of his predecessors .

claim: The Hundred Years' War includes a war.
evidence: Hundred Years' War Later historians adopted the term `` Hundred Years ' War '' as a historiography periodization to encompass all of these events , thus constructing the longest military conflict in European history . Hundred Years' War The Hundred Years ' War was a series of conflicts waged from 1337 to 1453 by the House of Plantagenet , rulers of the Kingdom of England , against the House of Valois , rulers of the Kingdom of France , over the succession of the French throne . Hundred Years' War Local conflicts in neighbouring areas , which were contemporarily related to the war , including the War of the Breton Succession 1341 -- 1364 , the Castilian Civil War 1366 -- 1369 , the War of the Two Peters 1356 -- 1375 in Aragon , and the 1383 -- 85 Crisis in Portugal , were availed by the parties to advance their agendas . Hundred Years' War The war marked both the height of chivalry and its subsequent decline , and the development of strong national identities in both countries . Hundred Years' War The dissatisfaction of English nobles , resulting from the loss of their continental landholdings , became a factor leading to the civil wars known as the Wars of the Roses 1455 -- 1487 . Hundred Years' War The war owes its historical significance to multiple factors . Hundred Years' War Several overwhelming English victories in the war -- especially at Crecy , Poitiers , and Agincourt -- raised the prospects of an ultimate English triumph . Hundred Years' War Although primarily a dynastic conflict , the war gave impetus to ideas of French and English nationalism . Hundred Years' War Starting in 1429 , decisive French victories at , Patay , Formigny , and Castillon concluded the war in favour of France , with England permanently losing most of its major possessions on the continent . Hundred Years' War Historians commonly divide the war into three phases separated by truces : the Edwardian Era War 1337 -- 1360 ; the Caroline War 1369 -- 1389 ; and the Lancastrian War 1415 -- 1453 . Hundred Years' War Each side drew many allies into the war .

claim: Animals are part of the History of Earth.
evidence: Miocene The plants and animals of the Miocene were fairly modern . Multicellular organism All species of animals , land plants and most fungi are multicellular , as are many algae , whereas a few organisms are partially uni - and partially multicellular , like slime molds and social amoebae such as the genus Dictyostelium . History of Earth The earliest undisputed evidence of life on Earth dates at least from 3.5 billion years ago , during the Eoarchean Era after a geological crust started to solidify following the earlier molten Hadean Eon . History of Earth Life remained mostly small and microscopic until about 580 million years ago , when complex multicellular life arose , developed over time , and culminated in the Cambrian Explosion about 541 million years ago . History of Earth This event drove a rapid diversification of life forms on Earth that produced most of the major phyla known today ; and it marked the end of the Proterozoic Eon and the beginning of the Cambrian Period of the Paleozoic Era . History of Earth Hominins , the earliest direct ancestors of the human clade , rose sometime during the latter part of the Miocene epoch ; the precise time marking the first hominins is broadly debated over a current range of 13 to 4 mya . Life Various forms of life exist , such as plants , animals , fungi , protists , archaea , and bacteria .

claim: James VI and I was a person.
evidence: James VI and I Since the latter half of the 20th century , historians have tended to revise James 's reputation and treat him as a serious and thoughtful monarch . James VI and I In his reign , the Plantation of Ulster and British colonization of the Americas began . James VI and I James VI and I 19 June 1566 -- 27 March 1625 was King of Scotland as James VI from 24 July 1567 and King of England and Ireland as James I from the union of the Scottish and English crowns on 24 March 1603 until his death . James VI and I He was a major advocate of a single parliament for England and Scotland . James VI and I In 1603 , he succeeded the last Tudor monarch of England and Ireland , Elizabeth I , who died without issue . James VI and I After the Union of the Crowns , he based himself in England the largest of the three realms from 1603 , only returning to Scotland once in 1617 , and styled himself `` King of Great Britain and Ireland '' . James VI and I Four different regents governed during his minority , which ended officially in 1578 , though he did not gain full control of his government until 1583 . James VI and I Sir Anthony Weldon claimed that James had been termed `` the wisest fool in Christendom '' , an epithet associated with his character ever since . James VI and I He continued to reign in all three kingdoms for 22 years , a period known after him as the Jacobean era , until his death in 1625 at the age of 58 . James VI and I James succeeded to the Scottish throne at the age of thirteen months , after his mother Mary was compelled to abdicate in his favour . James VI and I He sponsored the translation of the Bible that would later be named after him : the Authorised King James Version . James VI and I He achieved most of his aims in Scotland but faced great difficulties in England , including the Gunpowder Plot in 1605 and repeated conflicts with the English Parliament . James VI and I James was the son of Mary , Queen of Scots , and a great-great-grandson of Henry VII , King of England and Lord of Ireland , positioning him to eventually accede to all three thrones . James VI and I James himself was a talented scholar , the author of works such as Daemonologie 1597 , The True Law of Free Monarchies 1598 , and Basilikon Doron 1599 . James VI and I At 57 years and 246 days , James 's reign in Scotland was longer than those of any of his predecessors . James VI and I Under James , the `` Golden Age '' of Elizabethan literature and drama continued , with writers such as William Shakespeare , John Donne , Ben Jonson , and Sir Francis Bacon contributing to a flourishing literary culture .
